-- Divide-by-zero TRAP probe. The divisor is a clogger byte; fed a zero byte it
-- is a runtime division by zero. Both the C bootstrap and the native ELF must
-- fault CLEANLY: nonzero exit, empty stdout, NO SIGFPE/#DE crash. (The native
-- back end guards with `test rcx,rcx; jz <exit1>` before `div`.) Graded for
-- exit-status parity vs C; C also prints `herbert: line N: division by zero`,
-- the native side matches exit + empty stdout (exact-stderr text deferred, D13).
func main():
    let inp = clogger()
    let a = index(inp, 0)
    let b = index(inp, 1)
    return a / b
end
